    "body": "Very often the documentation badge on `develop` says *failing*. The cause is the time it takes to build the docs, that may exceed the maximum allowed on readthedocs (15 min.) An example of a failing build is [here](https://readthedocs.org/projects/spack/builds/6518192/).\r\n\r\n### Expected Result\r\n\r\nA  documentation badge that says *passing* - in line with the \"docs\" unit test that passed on Travis\r\n\r\n### Actual Result\r\n\r\nSometimes we have a *passing* result, sometimes a *failing*, depending whether or not readthedocs can build our documentation in less than 15 min.",
